  "texts": [
    "These clients hold 20k data samples in total.",
    "During the evaluation, we consider two types of benchmarks, including closeended benchmarks and open-ended benchmarks.",
    "We choose MMLU [73] (knowledge), BBH [74] (reasoning), DROP [75] (reasoning), HumanEval [76] (coding), and CRASS [77] (counterfact) for close-ended evaluation [78], Vicuna-Bench [42] and MT-Bench [79] for open-ended evaluation.",
    "Note that MT-Bench is currently one of the most common benchmarks for evaluating instruction-following capability, which involves evaluations of two-turn conversations.Experimental results.",
    "Table 4 shows the performance of local training and 7 FL algorithms trained on general dataset, where 9 metrics are reported for comprehensive comparisons."
  ],
